[Dr Pfeffer's response to our request for information and his useful data,
particularly regarding camelpox, are timely and gratefully
acknowledged. Hopefully, someone in the Saudi Ministry of Agriculture
(which reportedly has been notified about the cases) will be able to
enlighten us on the investigations and their results.
Regarding the presence of LSD in the Arabian peninsula, the reader is
referred to OIE's epidemiological data. According to those, LSD has been
recorded and reported in Bahrein (1993, 1994, 2002, 2003); Kuwait (1991);
Oman (1994); and the United Arab Emirates (2000). These might have been
introductions from Eastern Africa by imported cattle for slaughter. See
<http://www.oie.int/hs2/sit_mald_freq_pl.asp?c_cont=3&c_mald=8>. - Mod.AS]
